select
  s.id, 'board', NULL, 'ผู้ป่วยอายุ 65 ปี chronic alcohol use + cirrhosis + esophageal varices on propranolol + EVBL + adherent — มา clinic for routine surveillance

คำถาม: HCC surveillance + cirrhosis management principles', '[{"label":"A","text":"No surveillance needed"},{"label":"B","text":"**Cirrhosis comprehensive management + HCC surveillance**: (1) **HCC surveillance** in cirrhosis: - US ± AFP q6 months for at-risk (cirrhosis any etiology, chronic HBV without cirrhosis if Asian male > 40 / Asian female > 50 / Africans > 20 / family history HCC) - Multi-phase contrast CT or MRI if US suboptimal (obesity, fatty liver) or lesion detected - LI-RADS classification for indeterminate lesions; (2) **Variceal surveillance**: - EGD at diagnosis of cirrhosis - Repeat per Baveno criteria: small varices, no red signs → 2 yr; large or red signs → primary prophylaxis (NSBB or band) - On secondary prophylaxis (post-bleed, this patient) → continue NSBB + serial banding until eradication; (3) **Treat underlying liver disease**: - HBV: antiviral lifelong - HCV: DAA eradication (cure > 95%) - Alcohol: cessation absolute - NAFLD/MASH: weight loss, GLP-1 agonist (semaglutide, tirzepatide), pioglitazone (selected), resmetirom (FDA-approved 2024 for non-cirrhotic MASH) - Autoimmune: immunosuppression; (4) **Decompensation management**: - Ascites: sodium restriction (2 g/d) + diuretic (spironolactone + furosemide 100:40 ratio); refractory → large-volume paracentesis + albumin replacement; TIPS for refractory; - SBP prophylaxis if ascites + low protein or prior SBP — ciprofloxacin or TMP-SMX or norfloxacin daily - Hepatic encephalopathy: lactulose + rifaximin; treat precipitants - HRS: vasopressor (terlipressin, midodrine + octreotide + albumin) + RRT bridge; transplant - HPS (hepatopulmonary syndrome) — transplant evaluation; (5) **Liver transplant evaluation**: - MELD-Na score (waitlist priority US) - Refer when MELD > 15, refractory complications, HCC within criteria - Comprehensive evaluation: cardiac, pulm, infectious, psychosocial, cancer; (6) **Nutrition**: high-calorie + high-protein (1.2-1.5 g/kg); avoid restrictive low-protein (worsens malnutrition + encephalopathy); zinc, vitamin D, thiamine; (7) **Vaccinations** (inactivated): HAV, HBV, pneumococcal, influenza, COVID, Tdap; (8) **Lifestyle**: absolute alcohol cessation, smoking cessation, weight management (NAFLD), exercise; (9) **Avoid hepatotoxic medications**: NSAIDs (renal + bleeding), high-dose acetaminophen (2 g/day max in cirrhotic), aminoglycosides; (10) **Frailty + sarcopenia** — assessment + intervention"},{"label":"C","text":"Refer to hospice"},{"label":"D","text":"Stop all medications"},{"label":"E","text":"Annual labs only"}]'::jsonb,
  'B', '**Cirrhosis comprehensive management** — multidimensional. **HCC surveillance** (AASLD): US ± AFP q6 mo for cirrhosis + at-risk HBV. Sensitivity ~ 60-80% (US alone); higher with AFP. Multi-phase CT/MRI for diagnosis with LI-RADS. **Variceal surveillance** (Baveno VII): - EGD at diagnosis - Small varices no red signs: q2 yr - Medium/large or red signs: primary prophylaxis (NSBB — carvedilol preferred per recent data, or EVBL) - Secondary: NSBB + EVBL until eradication **Decompensation management**: - Ascites: Na restriction + diuretic; TIPS for refractory; albumin with LVP - SBP: prophylaxis ciprofloxacin/norfloxacin/TMP-SMX in at-risk - Encephalopathy: lactulose + rifaximin; precipitants - HRS: terlipressin + albumin; transplant - Portal HTN: TIPS for refractory complications **Transplant evaluation**: MELD-Na > 15, refractory complications, HCC within criteria. **Underlying disease specific**: HBV antiviral, HCV DAA cure, alcohol cessation, NAFLD weight loss + emerging therapies (resmetirom FDA 2024 for non-cirrhotic MASH; semaglutide promising), AIH/PBC/PSC immunosuppression. **Nutrition**: do NOT restrict protein (worsens sarcopenia + encephalopathy); 1.2-1.5 g/kg; zinc, vit D, thiamine. **Vaccinations inactivated**. **Avoid hepatotoxic**: NSAIDs, high acetaminophen, aminoglycosides. **Frailty + sarcopenia**: Liver Frailty Index (LFI); intervention.', NULL,
  'medium', 'gi', 'review',
  'surgery', 'clinical_decision', 'gi', 'adult',
  'AASLD Cirrhosis 2021; Baveno VII 2022; AASLD HCC 2023; EASL Guidelines', 'AI-generated-board-seed', true, 'seeded via Claude Code session (no critique pass)'
from public.mcq_subjects s
where s.name = 'surg_clinical_decision'
  and s.audience = 'board'
  and not exists (
    select 1 from public.mcq_questions q
    where q.exam_source = 'AI-generated-board-seed'
      and q.board_specialty = 'surgery'
      and q.scenario = 'ผู้ป่วยอายุ 65 ปี chronic alcohol use + cirrhosis + esophageal varices on propranolol + EVBL + adherent — มา clinic for routine surveillance

คำถาม: HCC surveillance + cirrhosis management principles'
  );

