select
  s.id, 'board', NULL, 'Basic science: surgical pharmacology + drug interactions

คำถาม: perioperative medication management', '[{"label":"A","text":"Continue all medications"},{"label":"B","text":"**Perioperative medication management — specific decisions**: (1) **Antihypertensives**: - **ACE-I / ARB**: HOLD on day of surgery — intraoperative hypotension; resume post-op when hemodynamically stable - **Beta-blocker**: CONTINUE if chronic; DO NOT initiate new (POISE — increased death + stroke) - **Calcium channel blocker**: continue - **Diuretic**: hold day of surgery typically (volume + electrolyte) - **Clonidine** (α2-agonist): continue (withdrawal rebound HTN); (2) **Antidiabetic**: - **Metformin**: usually OK day before; hold day of surgery for major (lactic acidosis risk if CKD); - **Sulfonylureas**: hold day of surgery (hypoglycemia) - **SGLT2 inhibitor (canagliflozin, empagliflozin, dapagliflozin)**: HOLD 3-4 days pre-op (DKA risk — euglycemic DKA can occur with normal glucose; FDA warning) - **GLP-1 (semaglutide, liraglutide, tirzepatide)**: HOLD 1 week pre-op for daily, 2 weeks for weekly (delayed gastric emptying → aspiration risk during anesthesia — ASA + ASRA guidance 2023) - **DPP-4 inhibitor (sitagliptin)**: usually continue - **Insulin**: long-acting reduced dose night before + day of, short-acting hold day of, sliding scale + correction; (3) **Anticoagulant + antiplatelet**: see prior question on perioperative anticoagulation; (4) **Statin**: CONTINUE — perioperative cardiovascular protection; (5) **Hormonal**: - **OCP, HRT**: VTE risk — consider holding 4 weeks pre-op for major + immobilization vs continuing in lower-risk - **Tamoxifen, AI**: continue (long half-life, low impact); - **GnRH agonist**: continue; (6) **Psychiatric**: - **SSRIs**: continue (rebound depression); some bleeding risk - **SNRIs**: continue - **MAOIs**: HOLD 2 weeks pre-op if possible (severe drug interaction with sympathomimetics, meperidine, opioid) - **TCAs**: continue typically - **Lithium**: hold day of surgery + monitor electrolyte (renal); - **Antipsychotics**: continue (avoid withdrawal); (7) **Antiepileptics**: continue (perioperative seizure prevention); IV equivalent if NPO; (8) **Immunosuppressants** (transplant, autoimmune): continue (avoid rejection / flare); stress-dose steroid if chronic; (9) **Steroids**: - Stress dose if HPA suppression suspected (chronic ≥ 20 mg prednisone or equivalent × 3 weeks within last year — debated, modern less aggressive per Marik) - Continue or supplement during surgery + post-op taper; (10) **Herbal supplements**: - Hold 1-2 weeks pre-op: ginkgo, garlic, ginseng, ginger (bleeding); St. John''s wort (drug interactions); kava, valerian (sedation); ephedra (sympathomimetic - banned); echinacea (immune modulation); (11) **NSAIDs**: hold 5-7 days pre-op for elective; aspirin individualized; (12) **Antiretrovirals (HIV)**: continue (avoid resistance); coordinate with ID + pharmacist for drug interactions; (13) **Opioids** (chronic use, addiction recovery): continue baseline + multimodal adjuncts; addiction medicine consult; (14) **Pre-op assessment + medication reconciliation** essential; pharmacist consultation in complex polypharmacy"},{"label":"C","text":"Stop all medications 4 weeks before"},{"label":"D","text":"Start all medications day of surgery"},{"label":"E","text":"No medication review needed"}]'::jsonb,
  'B', '**Perioperative medication management** — common source of errors; impacts outcomes. **Categories** (continue, hold, modify): 1. **HOLD** day of surgery: ACE-I/ARB, sulfonylureas, SGLT2, GLP-1 (1-2 weeks), diuretics (variable), most NSAIDs (elective), warfarin (5 days), DOACs (1-2 days based on procedure), oral hypoglycemics (mostly day of) 2. **CONTINUE** through surgery: beta-blocker (if chronic), statin, ACE-I/ARB sometimes for HF (newer evidence — controversy), SSRIs, antiepileptics, antipsychotics, immunosuppressants, antiretrovirals, calcium channel blockers, antiparkinsonian (don''t withdraw — worsening symptoms) 3. **MODIFY**: insulin (reduce long-acting + hold short-acting + sliding scale day of), steroids (stress dose if HPA-suppressed) **Key specifics — recent updates**: - **SGLT2 inhibitors**: HOLD 3-4 days pre-op due to euglycemic DKA risk (FDA warning + clinical case series) - **GLP-1 agonists**: HOLD 1 week for daily formulations, 2 weeks for weekly (semaglutide, dulaglutide, tirzepatide) due to delayed gastric emptying + aspiration risk (ASA + ASRA 2023 guidance) - **Beta-blocker**: continue if chronic; DO NOT INITIATE NEW perioperatively (POISE trial NEJM 2008 — increased death + stroke) - **Aspirin**: continue except for high-bleed surgery (intracranial, posterior chamber eye, transurethral prostate); POISE-2 supported continuation generally **Steroid stress dose**: traditional approach for chronic ≥ 20 mg prednisone or equivalent × 3 weeks within last year — debated; modern approach: hydrocortisone 50-100 mg pre-op + post-op taper; some prefer simpler ''continue usual dose'' approach with monitoring (Marik + others suggested over-treatment historically). **Herbal supplements**: many affect bleeding (gingko, garlic, ginseng, ginger), sedation (kava, valerian), HPA (ginseng, licorice), drug interactions (St. John''s wort) — hold 1-2 weeks pre-op. **Anesthesia + drug interactions**: MAOI + sympathomimetic + meperidine (serotonin syndrome) — hold MAOI 2 weeks if possible; antiretroviral + opioid metabolism considerations; pharmacist consultation for polypharmacy. **Reconciliation** at admission + discharge — important to prevent omission + duplication. **Patient education** — clear instructions for what to take/not take morning of surgery.', NULL,
  'medium', 'endocrine_metabolic', 'review',
  'surgery', 'basic_science', 'endocrine_metabolic', 'adult',
  'ASA Perioperative Medication Management; ASRA + ASA GLP-1 + SGLT2 Statements 2023; ACCP Perioperative Anticoagulation', 'AI-generated-board-seed', true, 'seeded via Claude Code session (no critique pass)'
