select
  s.id, 'board', NULL, 'Basic science: surgical complications + classification systems

คำถาม: classification of surgical complications + reporting', '[{"label":"A","text":"No classification needed"},{"label":"B","text":"**Surgical complications — standardized classification + reporting**: (1) **Clavien-Dindo Classification** — universal language for postoperative complications based on therapy required: - **Grade I**: any deviation from normal post-op course without need for pharmacologic intervention beyond antiemetic, antipyretic, diuretic, electrolyte, physiotherapy (e.g., wound infection treated bedside) - **Grade II**: requires pharmacologic intervention (antibiotic, transfusion, TPN) - **Grade IIIa**: intervention not requiring general anesthesia (bedside drainage, IR procedure) - **Grade IIIb**: intervention requiring general anesthesia (return to OR) - **Grade IVa**: life-threatening complication requiring ICU with single organ dysfunction - **Grade IVb**: multi-organ dysfunction in ICU - **Grade V**: death; (2) **Comprehensive Complication Index (CCI)** — Slankamenac et al — sums all complications weighted by severity → single score 0-100; more granular than reporting only most severe; useful for research + comparison; (3) **Definition of specific complications**: - **SSI (CDC NHSN)**: superficial, deep, organ/space - **Anastomotic leak** — defect in suture line with extravasation - **Pneumonia** — multiple criteria - **AKI (KDIGO)** — Cr rise + UO criteria; staging - **DVT/PE** — confirmed - **Sepsis** (Sepsis-3): organ dysfunction from dysregulated host response - **Postoperative MI** — troponin + symptoms/ECG/imaging - **Delirium** (CAM); (4) **ACS NSQIP** — risk-adjusted outcomes benchmarking; standardized data collection: 30-day outcomes (mortality, complications), risk stratification, hospital comparison feedback; (5) **STS National Database** (cardiothoracic specific), MBSAQIP (bariatric), TSACO (Trauma Surgery + Critical Care Open), NTDB (trauma); (6) **Outcome reporting** principles: - Define complications upfront - Capture all (under-reporting bias) - Risk-adjust for fair comparison - Include long-term + patient-reported outcomes - Quality of life metrics; (7) **Reporting frameworks**: - **STROBE** (observational) - **CONSORT** (RCTs) - **PRISMA** (systematic reviews/meta-analyses) - **CARE** (case reports) - **IDEAL** (surgical innovation); (8) **Internal hospital reporting**: M&M conferences, incident reports, quality committees; (9) **External reporting**: NSQIP feedback, accreditation (Joint Commission, ACS), CMS measures, public reporting (mixed evidence on impact); (10) **Use of data**: quality improvement, individual surgeon feedback, certification + maintenance of certification, research, peer review"},{"label":"C","text":"Ad hoc reporting only"},{"label":"D","text":"Avoid complications mention"},{"label":"E","text":"Single metric for all surgery"}]'::jsonb,
  'B', '**Standardized surgical complication classification + reporting** — essential for quality improvement + research + benchmarking. **Clavien-Dindo Classification** (Dindo D et al, Ann Surg 2004) — universal language for surgical complications, based on therapy intensity required to manage. Validated, simple, widely adopted globally. **Grades I-V** as described. **CCI (Comprehensive Complication Index)** — Slankamenac et al — improvement over reporting most severe complication only; sums all complications weighted by severity (Clavien-Dindo grade × frequency) → 0-100 score. More accurate reflection of complication burden; useful for research comparing groups. **Specific complication definitions** — standardized definitions improve consistency: - **SSI** — CDC NHSN: superficial (within 30 days, involving skin + subQ), deep (≥ 30 days or up to 90 days with implant, involves fascia + muscle), organ/space (deeper) - **Anastomotic leak** — definition varies by anatomy; consensus statements exist for specific procedures (rectal, esophageal, gastric, etc.) - **AKI** — KDIGO: ≥ 0.3 mg/dL Cr increase within 48h OR ≥ 1.5× baseline within 7 days OR UO < 0.5 mL/kg/h × 6h; staging 1-3 - **Sepsis-3** (2016) — life-threatening organ dysfunction from dysregulated host response to infection; SOFA score change ≥ 2 - **Septic shock** — vasopressor needed for MAP ≥ 65 + lactate > 2 despite fluid - **MI (4th universal definition)** — troponin + ischemia evidence (symptoms, ECG, imaging) - **Delirium** — CAM or CAM-ICU **Quality improvement databases**: 1. **ACS NSQIP** — National Surgical Quality Improvement Program — risk-adjusted outcomes; benchmark + feedback; participating hospitals improve over time; > 800 hospitals globally 2. **STS National Database** — cardiothoracic 3. **MBSAQIP** — bariatric 4. **VSGNE** — vascular New England 5. **TQIP** — trauma 6. **NTDB** — National Trauma Data Bank **Research reporting standards** (EQUATOR Network): - **CONSORT** — randomized trials - **STROBE** — observational - **PRISMA** — systematic reviews + meta-analyses - **CARE** — case reports - **STROCSS** — surgical case series - **IDEAL** — surgical innovation - **TRIPOD** — prediction models **Risk adjustment** — important for fair comparison; ASA class, comorbidities, age, urgency adjust for case mix. **Patient-reported outcomes (PROs)** — increasingly emphasized: quality of life, functional outcomes, satisfaction; complement traditional clinical endpoints.', NULL,
  'easy', 'procedures', 'review',
  'surgery', 'basic_science', 'procedures', 'adult',
  'Dindo D et al. Ann Surg 2004 (Clavien-Dindo); Slankamenac K et al. Ann Surg (CCI); ACS NSQIP', 'AI-generated-board-seed', true, 'seeded via Claude Code session (no critique pass)'
