select
  s.id, 'board', NULL, 'ระบบ EMS: surgical leadership + team dynamics

คำถาม: surgical leadership + team performance', '[{"label":"A","text":"Single individual responsibility"},{"label":"B","text":"**Surgical leadership + team-based care — modern paradigm**: (1) **Team-based care benefits**: - Better outcomes (multiple studies — colorectal ERAS, cardiac surgery teams, trauma teams) - Improved safety - Higher patient satisfaction - Reduced provider burnout - Enhanced learning environment; (2) **OR team composition**: surgeon (attending + assistants + trainees), anesthesia (attending + residents/CRNAs), nursing (circulating + scrub), technicians, perfusionist (cardiac), industry reps (selected), residents/students/observers — clear roles + communication; (3) **Crew Resource Management (CRM)** — borrowed from aviation: - Mutual support + team awareness - Shared mental model - Closed-loop communication (''Hand me the suture'' → ''Suture handing now'' → ''Got it'') - Speaking up culture (encourage all team members to raise concerns) - Briefing + debriefing; (4) **WHO Surgical Safety Checklist** — see prior question; (5) **Briefings + debriefings**: - Pre-procedure briefing: discuss plan, anticipated challenges, equipment, roles - Post-procedure debriefing: what went well, what could improve, learnings; (6) **Communication tools**: - SBAR — situation/background/assessment/recommendation - I-PASS (handoff) - CUS — concerned/uncomfortable/stop (escalation language) - Closed-loop communication for orders + actions; (7) **Leadership principles in surgery**: - **Servant leadership** vs traditional hierarchical - **Psychological safety** — Edmondson''s work; teams that learn + innovate require team members able to take interpersonal risks - **Inclusive leadership** — value all team members'' input - **Just culture** — distinguish system from individual error; encourage reporting + learning - **Emotional intelligence** — self-awareness, self-regulation, motivation, empathy, social skills - **Adaptive leadership** — respond to changing conditions; (8) **Training in non-technical skills (NOTSS)**: - Decision-making, situation awareness, communication, teamwork, leadership - Increasingly assessed in residency + maintenance of certification - Simulation training + debriefing; (9) **Diversity, equity, inclusion**: - Diverse teams perform better (multiple evidence) - Representation across roles + leadership - Addressing bias (implicit, structural) - Cultural competency - Inclusive language + behaviors; (10) **Conflict management**: respectful disagreement, principled negotiation, focus on patient care, after-action reviews; (11) **Mentorship + sponsorship**: structured mentorship programs; sponsorship advocates for opportunities; impact on career trajectory + retention; (12) **Quality improvement leadership**: data-driven, PDSA, lean/six-sigma methodologies; team-based QI; (13) **Resilience + wellbeing**: leaders model wellbeing + advocate for team wellness"},{"label":"C","text":"Authoritarian only"},{"label":"D","text":"No communication needed"},{"label":"E","text":"Avoid team interactions"}]'::jsonb,
  'B', '**Surgical leadership + team-based care** — modern foundation of high-performing surgical care. **Evidence for team-based care**: - Better outcomes (ERAS, trauma teams, ICU rounds, OR teams) - Improved safety + reduced errors - Higher patient satisfaction - Reduced burnout - Enhanced learning **Crew Resource Management (CRM)** — borrowed from aviation: shifted accident reduction by addressing human factors. Applied to medicine via Operating Room Briefings, Time Out, Debriefings, Closed-Loop Communication. **Key communication tools**: - **SBAR**: Situation, Background, Assessment, Recommendation - **I-PASS**: Illness severity, Patient summary, Action list, Situation awareness, Synthesis by receiver - **CUS**: Concerned, Uncomfortable, Safety issue/Stop the line - **Closed-loop**: sender → receiver acknowledges → sender confirms - **Read-back** for verbal orders, especially high-risk medications **Non-technical skills (NOTSS)** — surgeon-specific framework (Yule + Flin): 1. Situation awareness 2. Decision-making 3. Communication + teamwork 4. Leadership Increasingly assessed in training + practice; simulation + structured feedback. **Psychological safety** (Amy Edmondson, Harvard): team belief that it is safe for interpersonal risk-taking (asking questions, admitting mistakes, raising concerns). Predicts team learning + performance. Highest-performing teams have high psychological safety. **Just culture** (Marx, Reason): - Human error → console - At-risk behavior → coach - Reckless behavior → sanction - System problems → fix the system Encourages reporting + learning vs blame + cover-up. **Leadership styles** evolving from authoritative/hierarchical to: - Servant leadership - Transformational - Adaptive - Inclusive **Emotional intelligence (EQ)**: self-awareness, self-regulation, motivation, empathy, social skills (Goleman). Correlates with leadership effectiveness + team performance. **Diversity, Equity + Inclusion (DEI)**: - Diverse teams demonstrate better problem-solving + outcomes (McKinsey + others) - Underrepresentation in surgery (women, minorities, LGBTQ+) — ongoing efforts - Bias awareness + mitigation - Inclusive language + behavior - Mentorship + sponsorship for underrepresented **Burnout + wellbeing intersect with leadership**: leaders shape culture; model wellbeing; advocate for systems improvements; address workload + EHR + administrative burden. **Quality improvement leadership**: data-driven, PDSA cycles, lean/six sigma, team-based, learning health systems. **Conflict management**: principled negotiation (Fisher + Ury — separate people from problem, focus on interests not positions, generate options for mutual gain, use objective criteria), respectful disagreement focused on patient care, after-action reviews. **Mentorship**: structured programs reduce burnout, improve career trajectory, retain talent; sponsorship distinct from mentorship — sponsors advocate for opportunities.', NULL,
  'easy', 'procedures', 'review',
  'surgery', 'ems_mgmt', 'procedures', 'adult',
  'ACS NSQIP + Surgeon Leadership; Edmondson A. The Fearless Organization; Yule S, Flin R. NOTSS', 'AI-generated-board-seed', true, 'seeded via Claude Code session (no critique pass)'
from public.mcq_subjects s
